d 'BYPERRON': module to determine structural breaks in time series models (Bai-Perron, 2003; Yamamoto-Perron, 2013) 
d
d  byperron estimates and tests multiple structural changes in
d linear time series models, implementing both the classical time
d domain procedure of Bai and Perron (1998 & 2003) and its band
d spectral generalization by Yamamoto and Perron (2013). Three
d methods are provided: the full spectrum, which delivers the
d classical Bai-Perron tests and break dates; the truncated
d spectrum, which is robust to low frequency contamination of the
d errors such as level shifts, remaining trends or long memory; and
d a user-chosen frequency band, which tests stability at specific
d horizons such as business cycle frequencies. 
d
d KW: time series
d KW: structural breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260722
d
d Author: Ozan Eruygur,  Ankara Haci Bayram Veli University
d Support: email eruygur@@gmail.com
d
f byperron.ado
f byperron.sthlp
